    <header>
        <h1>H-S Minecraft MMO RPG</h1>
        <p>A custom-built MMORPG experience within Minecraft</p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Core Vision</h2>
            <p>H-S MMO is a complete reimagining of Minecraft as a true MMORPG, featuring:</p>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Persistent World</h3>
                    <p>A massive, hand-crafted world with distinct regions, dungeons, and hidden secrets.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Class System</h3>
                    <p>8 unique classes with skill trees and specialized abilities.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Quest System</h3>
                    <p>Over 200 planned quests with branching storylines and meaningful rewards.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Technical Implementation</h2>
            <p>Built using these core technologies:</p>
            <div style="margin: 20px 0;">
                <span class="tech-pill">Custom Java Plugin</span>
                <span class="tech-pill">MySQL Database</span>
                <span class="tech-pill">WorldEdit</span>
                <span class="tech-pill">Custom Resource Pack</span>
                <span class="tech-pill">BossBar API</span>
                <span class="tech-pill">Packet Manipulation</span>
            </div>
            <p>The MMO will run on dedicated hardware separate from our main survival server.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Class System</h2>
            <p>Choose from these specialized roles:</p>
            
            <div class="class-card">
                <h3>Warrior</h3>
                <p>Tank specialization with heavy armor and defensive abilities.</p>
                <div class="skill-tree">
                    <div class="skill">
                        <span class="skill-name">Shield Wall</span>: Reduce incoming damage by 50% for 5 seconds.
                    </div>
                    <div class="skill">
                        <span class="skill-name">Taunt</span>: Force enemies to attack you for 8 seconds.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="class-card">
                <h3>Arcane Archer</h3>
                <p>Ranged DPS with elemental arrows and mobility.</p>
                <div class="skill-tree">
                    <div class="skill">
                        <span class="skill-name">Frost Arrow</span>: Slow enemies by 30% for 4 seconds.
                    </div>
                    <div class="skill">
                        <span class="skill-name">Volley</span>: Fire 5 arrows in a cone.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Additional classes would go here -->
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Progression Systems</h2>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Leveling</h3>
                    <p>100 levels with increasing XP requirements. Gain stat points each level.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Gear Score</h3>
                    <p>Items have tiered rarity (Common to Legendary) with random attributes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Reputation</h3>
                    <p>Earn faction reputation for unique rewards and quests.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Quest System Details</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Main Storyline</strong>: 50+ quest epic narrative with cutscenes</li>
                <li><strong>Side Quests</strong>: Optional stories with unique rewards</li>
                <li><strong>Daily Quests</strong>: Repeatable objectives for consistent progression</li>
                <li><strong>Dungeon Quests</strong>: Multi-stage instanced content</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; background: #2a2a2a; padding: 15px; border-radius: 6px; border-left: 4px solid #d35400;">
                <h3>Example Quest: "The Lost Artifact"</h3>
                <p><strong>Level Requirement</strong>: 25+</p>
                <p><strong>Objectives</strong>:
                    <ol>
                        <li>Speak to Archmage Velyn in Stormspire</li>
                        <li>Recover the Ancient Tome from Duskwood Catacombs</li>
                        <li>Defeat the Lich guarding the artifact</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p><strong>Rewards</strong>: 1500 XP, +50 Stormspire Reputation, Tome of Arcane Knowledge (accessory)</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Development Timeline</h2>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-date">Q1 2025</div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <p>Core plugin architecture completed</p>
                        <p>First region (Stormspire Valley) terrain generation</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-date">Q2 2025</div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <p>Class system implementation (4/8 classes)</p>
                        <p>First 30 quests scripted</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-date">Q3 2025</div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <p>Closed alpha testing begins</p>
                        <p>Dungeon system implementation</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Join the Development</h2>
            <p>Interested in testing or contributing?</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="background: #d35400; display: inline-block; padding: 10px 25px; border-radius: 5px; color: white; text-decoration: none;">Contact Us</a>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Follow our development blog for weekly updates.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
